remarks.para:
The recommended implementation pattern is to declare with properties in the target type derived from  instance like:

private string CellsStr => Cells.ToString();
private string DigitsStr => Digits.ToString(", ");

And then override the property like:
public override FormatInterpolation FormatInterpolationParts => [new("en-US", [CellsStr, DigitsStr]), new("zh-CN", [CellsStr, DigitsStr])];
The culture name "en-US" and "zh-CN" stands for the target country or region is English and China (Mainland) respectively. If you don't determine which region should be declared, just remove suffixes like "US" and "CN".

Please note the type of this property is , which is not a plain string text.
However, you can specify the target value using interpolated strings like $"UniqueRectangle{Type}Step",
where the interpolation Type is an integer that describes the sub-type of the Unique Rectangle (e.g. 1-6 stands for UR type 1-6).
The format text will be expanded to this expression in runtime:

var formatText = ResourceDictionary.Get($"TechniqueFormat_UniqueRectangle{Type}Step");

You can use this value to get the final text:

var culture = ...; // The culture string.
var formatArguments = FormatInterpolationParts?.FirstOrDefault(culture).ResourcePlaceholderValues;
var description = Format.ToString(formatArguments);

See the documentation documents defined in method  to learn more information.

